    "decription": "PIR Motion Detector",
    "overview": "<p>Wireless Passive Infrared (PIR) Motion Detector<\/p>",
    "inclusion": "<ol><li>Prepare the Controller to include a unit to the network by adding it to a group (method of adding a node to the network). Refer to controller instructions.<\/li> <li>If your Controller supports Network Wide Inclusion (NWI) locate the WAPIRZ-1 near the proposed installation location. If not skip to Step 4.<\/li> <li>With your Controller in Inclusion mode, you should see an indication on your Controller that the \u201cdevice was included\u201d in the network. It should display binary switch \/ Linear. The LED will stop blinking. Skip to Step 10. If the LED does not stop blinking, relocate the WAPIRZ-1 to within 100 feet (line of sight) of a Z-Wave device or your hub and repeat Step 3. If the LED continues to blink, your Controller does not support NWI and continue with Step 4.<\/li> <li>Place the WAPIRZ-1 within 3 feet of the Controller.<\/li> <li>With your controller in Inclusion mode, depress the Tamper switch for 1 second then release.<\/li> <li>You should see an indication on your Controller that the \u201cdevice was included\u201d in the network. It should display binary switch \/ Linear. The LED will stop blinking.<\/li> <li>The device will appear in the list of Switches.<\/li> <\/ol>",
    "exclusion": "<ol><li>Set up the Z-Wave\u2122 Interface Controller into \u201cexclusion\u201d mode, and following its instruction to delete the WAPIRZ-1 from the controller.<\/li> <li>Press the Tamper switch of WAPIRZ-1 for 1 second and release to be excluded. The LED light will flash continuously when the sensor is in the Exclusion condition.<\/li> <\/ol>",
    "wakeup": "<p>Open the motion detector case to \u201cwake\u201d the unit. <\/p>",
